          "5 Python Programming News",
          "LMS logs, Code Submission",
          "[Code2Vec embeddings from Code Submissions]",
          "Representations based on logs have been popular… However, doing richer representations is still seen as a challenging problem.",
          "The creation of user embeddings based on embeddings of their code submissions.",
          "Code2vec embeddings are padded to 50 sentences and contain 100 dimensions (Words, Python Categories, Python Token Words and AST Nodes).\n\nCode submissions of learners are used to build a User Submission Matrix. These are flattened and a user embedding is created with 100 dimensions.\n\nVisualization is done using Principal Components of the 2 variables.\n\n",
          "Naive Bayes, MLP",
          "5-Fold Crosss-Validation",
          "",
          "Authors create an embedding structure called code2vec that is meant to represent code submissions.\n\nAfter identifying the best form of code embeddings, they use these as inputs for the user representation: user2code2vec\n\n",
          ""
