    {
      "id": "379fe3b3-f552-4c3e-ba3c-e3c5d905faf9",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors propose a new method to profile computer science students through embeddings. The idea is not only to predict whether a code submission is correct but also to create a student profile that allows for better and more adequate recommendations to the learner’s knowledge level. Authors identify the extraction of relevant student features as a limitation since, in LA, there is no such thing as an infinite amount of students to build embeddings from.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "379fe3b3-f552-4c3e-ba3c-e3c5d905faf9",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
